HEADWORD: Greengill
<hw>Green"gill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An oyster which has the gills tinged with a green pigment, said to
be due to an abnormal condition of the blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

